    "body": "## Problem\r\n`gx` relies on `exepath` to get the fullpath of `cmd.exe`, and that path must use `\\`; otherwise, luv's spawn will fail.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nRevert `slash_adjust` in `exepath`, so that it still respects 'shellslash'\r\n\r\nfix #39524\r\n<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-04T16:18:14Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39541#discussion_r3173250553"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39541"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3173250553"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "After slash normalization, `os_can_exe` no longer mixes `/` and `\\`, which is expected.\nBoth `exepath` and `jobstart` depend on `os_can_exe`. So if we only add `slash_adjust` in `exepath` (as in this PR), `jobstart` could still see `/`, like `C:/Windows/System32/cmd.exe` here.\nIf we add `slash_adjust` to `os_can_exe`, we’ll need to fix `nvim_prog` below, since it currently uses `/`.\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9734f33bc73250ead81ab143a52739de69652f79/test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua#L2954",
            "commit_id": "fff839ca045da9ddd0703db878aa41c22c1d44bf",
            "created_at": "2026-05-01T13:04:43Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -2936,7 +2936,7 @@ describe('API', function()\n       eq(1, api.nvim_get_current_buf())\n       eq(3, api.nvim_get_option_value('channel', { buf = 1 }))\n \n-      local info = term_channel_info(3, 1, { eval('exepath(&shell)') })\n+      local info = term_channel_info(3, 1, { t.fix_slashes(eval('exepath(&shell)')) })",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39541#discussion_r3173250553",
