            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I've reverted the `slash_adjust` in `exepath`.\r\n\r\nI also noticed an issue that already exists in the 0.12 release: if we run `:te` first and then `mksession`, it generated code like this:\r\n```vim\r\nif bufexists(fnamemodify(\"term://D:/a/neovim/neovim//1536:C:/WINDOWS/system32/cmd.exe\", \":p\")) | buffer term://D:/a/neovim/neovim//1536:C:/WINDOWS/system32/cmd.exe | else | edit term://D:/a/neovim/neovim//1536:C:/WINDOWS/system32/cmd.exe | endif\r\n```\r\nThis causes the terminal to exit when restoring the session (also due to `/`).\r\nWe might want to address this separately in the future—the root cause seems to be in `ses_escape_fname`:\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ec671a2d51d0418d9bb01bf17329fcc1e956004c/src/nvim/ex_session.c#L293-L298\r\n",
            "commit_id": "fff839ca045da9ddd0703db878aa41c22c1d44bf",
            "created_at": "2026-05-02T11:01:36Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -2936,7 +2936,7 @@ describe('API', function()\n       eq(1, api.nvim_get_current_buf())\n       eq(3, api.nvim_get_option_value('channel', { buf = 1 }))\n \n-      local info = term_channel_info(3, 1, { eval('exepath(&shell)') })\n+      local info = term_channel_info(3, 1, { t.fix_slashes(eval('exepath(&shell)')) })",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39541#discussion_r3176532688",
